or%20the%20economy%2C%20leaving%20key%20industries%20understaffed%2C%20and%20adding%20to%20the%20strain%20on%20government%20services%20and%20social%20safety%20nets%2C%20Graham%20and%20other%20experts%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSome%20of%20them%20drop%20out%20%5Bof%20college%5D%20and%20are%20just%20sort%20of%20forlorn%20and%20have%20no%20purpose%20or%20meaning%20in%20life.%20They're%20not%20very%20likely%20to%20be%20married.%20They're%20very%20likely%20to%20be%20living%20in%20their%20parent's%20basement%2C%26quot%3B%20Graham%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20lonely%2C%20they're%20isolated.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20economic%20burden%20can%20also%20compound%20through%20generations%2C%20she%20added%2C%20given%20that%20men%20who%20have%20exited%20the%20workforce%20tend%20to%20be%20lower-income%20and%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20report%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdisconnected-youth-a-tale-of-2-gen-zs-in-america-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emental%20and%20physical%20health%20problems%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20impact%20their%20children's%20ability%20to%20build%20wealth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZack%20Mabel%2C%20a%20research%20professor%20at%20Georgetown%20University%2C%20theorizes%20that%20falling%20labor%20force%20participation%20among%20young%20men%20could%20impact%20the%20economy%20for%20at%20least%20several%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20this%20point%2C%20it's%20a%20long%20trend%20over%20the%20course%20of%20multiple%20decades%20that%20does%20not%20appear%20to%20be%20improving%2C%20and%20could%20have%20real%20long-term%20consequences%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2221b7ceb6-5c10-4411-8bf5-94b94fe51a82%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EStraining%20the%20economy%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20economy%20appears%20to%20already%20be%20feeling%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyoung-men-work-less-financially-independent-salary-marriageability-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edecline%20in%20male%20workforce%20participation%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Despite%20a%20small%20post-pandemic%20rebound%2C%20US%20GDP%20per%20employee%20fell%201%25%20in%202022%2C%20the%20first%20decline%20seen%20since%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdata.worldbank.org%2Findicator%2FSL.GDP.PCAP.EM.KD%3Flocations%3DUS%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWorld%20Bank%3C%2Fa%3E%20began%20recording%20productivity%20data%20over%2030%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20overall%20labor%20force%20participation%20rate%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20has%20slumped%20to%2062%25.%20Besides%20the%20years%20following%20the%20pandemic%2C%20US%20workforce%20participation%20rate%20hasn't%20been%20that%20low%20since%20the%2070s%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdata.worldbank.org%2Findicator%2FSL.TLF.CACT.NE.ZS%3Flocations%3DUS%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWorld%20Bank%20data%3C%2Fa%3E%20shows.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20trend%20could%20weigh%20on%20key%20industries%2C%20like%20infrastructure%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-is-experiencing-factory-boom-but-finding-workers-is-difficult-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emanufacturing%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20women%20are%20often%20less%20likely%20to%20seek%20work%20due%20to%20social%20stigma%2C%20Mabel%20said.%20That%20means%20it%20could%20be%20hard%20for%20those%20industries%20to%20find%20workers%2C%20which%20is%20a%20big%20problem%20considering%20the%20need%20for%20labor%20in%20growing%20areas%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsemiconductor-chips-jobs-hiring-arizona-tech-phoenix-tsmc-intel-china-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esemiconductors%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20a%20situation%20where%20you%20have%20millions%20of%20men%20%E2%80%A6%20foregoing%20college%2C%20and%20as%20a%20result%20are%20less%20productive%20and%20less%20able%20to%20hold%20onto%20a%20stable%20job%2C%20yes%2C%20that%20certainly%20would%20raise%20concerns%20our%20national%20productivity%20would%20suffer%20as%20a%20result%2C%26quot%3B%20Mabel%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20while%20the%20housing%20market%20may%20be%20booming%20now%2C%20it%20is%20also%20possible%20that%20men%20leaving%20the%20labor%20force%20will%20weigh%20on%20that%20market%20as%20well.%20Meredith%20Whitney%2C%20a%20longtime%20Wall%20Street%20forecaster%2C%20predicts%20home%20prices%20could%20drop%20as%20much%20as%2030%25%20over%20a%20period%20of%20years%20thanks%20to%20men%20working%20less%2C%20being%20less%20interested%20in%20starting%20families%2C%20and%20being%20more%20likely%20to%20live%20with%20their%20parents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20trends%20all%20weigh%20on%20household%20formation%2C%20which%20is%20the%20most%20important%20factor%20in%20determining%20home%20prices%20over%20the%20long%20term%2C%20Whitney%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E42%25%20of%20men%20who%20have%20exited%20the%20workforce%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brookings.edu%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F08%2Fes_81717who_is_out_of_the_labor_force_analysis.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elive%20with%20at%20least%20one%20parent%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%202017%20Brookings%20study%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20such%20a%20seismic%20shift%20in%20the%20social%20structure%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20hard%20to%20say%20how%20long%20it%20lasts.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGovernment%20benefits%20are%20also%20hugely%20taxed%20by%20men%20who%20are%20not%20in%20the%20workforce.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMen%20who%20have%20dropped%20out%20of%20the%20workforce%2C%20for%20one%2C%20are%20significantly%20more%20likely%20to%20suffer%20from%20opioid%20addiction%2C%20Graham%20said.%2044%25%20of%20men%20who%20were%20out%20of%20the%20workforce%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC6364990%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethey%20needed%20to%20take%20pain%20medication%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20more%20than%20double%20the%20portion%20recorded%20in%20employed%20men%2C%20where%20just%2020%25%20took%20pain%20meds%2C%20a%20separate%20Brookings%20study%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E57%25%20of%20men%20not%20looking%20for%20work%20said%20they%20had%20a%20physical%2C%20mental%2C%20or%20behavioral%20reason%2C%20according%20to%20a%20survey%20conducted%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbipartisanpolicy.org%2Freport%2Fbpc-artemis-survey%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBPC-Artemis%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E11%25%20of%20men%20who%20have%20exited%20the%20labor%20force%20rely%20entirely%20on%20government%20welfare%20programs%20for%20income%2C%20according%20to%20Brookings%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20cost%20the%20health%20system.%20They%20go%20to%20the%20emergency%20room%20and%20they're%20sick%2C%20they're%20not%20going%20to%20be%20able%20to%20pay%20the%20bills%2C%26quot%3B%20Graham%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20coming%20out%20of%20somewhere.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20welfare%20burden%20is%20exacerbated%20by%20the%20fact%20that%20unemployed%20men%20aren't%20contributing%20to%20benefit%20programs%20such%20as%20through%20Social%20Security%20taxes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPotentially%2C%20more%20and%20more%20people%20would%20benefit%20and%20depend%20on%20resources%20that%20we%20don't%20actually%20have%20the%20means%20to%20provide%20...%20And%20that%20then%20would%20really%20present%20itself%20as%20a%20huge%20societal%20conundrum%2C%26quot%3B%20Mabel%20warned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20no%20clear%20answer%20for%20how%20to%20get%20young%20men%20back%20into%20the%20workforce.%20The%20causes%20appear%20to%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femployment-young-men-labor-force-jobs-unemployment-insurance-hiring-2024-5%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAnd%252052%2525%2520of%2520men%252016%2Cenough%2520to%2520draw%2520them%2520in.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emultifold%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20disabilities%