ver%20to%20Business%20Insider%2C%20I%20was%20very%20happy%20to%20let%20finding%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fbest-robot-vacuum%5C%22%3Ebest%20robot%20vacuums%3C%2Fa%3E%20be%20someone%20else's%20job.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday's%20robot%20vacuums%20have%20more%20features%20than%20ever.%20Many%20are%20self-emptying%2C%20most%20have%20advanced%20mapping%20technology%20that%20allows%20you%20to%20clean%20your%20whole%20home%20or%20a%20single%20room%2C%20and%20mopping%20features%20are%20integrated%20more%20seamlessly.%20When%20an%20opportunity%20came%20up%20to%20test%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbi-auto-70244-20%26h%3D0beb8925063d36ab5f3b7e1604beb9e267bfee934a1c1a487ae102db5a30122e%26postID%3D6655db8542ab0c2431cbc960%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Fhome%252Fshark-matrix-plus-2-in-1-robot-vacuum-mop-review%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.amazon.com%252Fdp%252FB0B8B6N2G4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EShark%20Matrix%20Plus%202-in-1%20Robot%20Vacuum%20and%20Mop%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20has%20all%20the%20aforementioned%20features%2C%20I%20decided%20it%20was%20time%20to%20dip%20my%20toes%20back%20into%20the%20world%20of%20robot%20vacuums%20and%20see%20if%20the%20landscape%20had%20finally%20changed%20for%20the%20better.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20tested%20the%20Shark%20Matrix%20Plus%20in%20my%201%2C650-square-foot%20home%20over%20the%20course%20of%20six%20months.%20Despite%20a%20few%20cons%2C%20I%20really%20love%20this%20vacuum.%20It's%20saved%20me%20tons%20of%20time%2C%20and%20my%20floors%20have%20never%20looked%20cleaner.%20Read%20on%20for%20my%20full%20experience%20testing%20the%20Shark%20Matrix%20Plus%202-in-1%20Robot%20Vacuum.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Setup%20and%20design%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ESetup%20and%20design%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22side%20by%20side%20showing%20the%20shark%20matrix%20robot%20vacuum%20in%20a%20box%20next%20to%20it%20all%20set%20up%20on%20a%20hardwood%20floor%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6655e0fba961b37edf3a3a01%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EInstallation%20was%20straightforward%3A%20just%20remove%20the%20components%20from%20the%20box%20(left)%20and%20set%20up%20the%20base%20and%20robot%20in%20an%20empty%20corner%20of%20the%20house%20(right).%3Cp%3ELauren%20Savoie%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Shark%20Matrix%20Plus%202-in-1%20Robot%20Vacuum%20has%20four%20main%20components%3A%20the%20robot%2C%20its%20self-emptying%20docking%20base%2C%20a%20vacuum%20attachment%2C%20and%20a%20mopping%20attachment.%20Each%20of%20those%20main%20components%20has%20several%20smaller%20pieces%20to%20install.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20robot%20itself%20has%20a%20main%20brush%20roll%20and%20a%20side%20brush%20for%20sweeping%20debris%20out%20of%20corners.%20The%20robot%20has%20a%20circular%20design%20with%20two%20big%20wheels%20and%20two%20smaller%20wheels%20for%20nimble%20navigation.%20Compared%20to%20other%20robot%20vacuums%20I've%20seen%2C%20the%20brush%20roll%20is%20quite%20small%2C%20at%20exactly%206%20inches.%20iRobot%20models%2C%20by%20comparison%2C%20typically%20have%20two%20brush%20rolls%2C%20up%20to%209.5%20inches%20each.%20A%20longer%20brush%20roll%20usually%20translates%20to%20faster%20and%20more%20thorough%20cleaning%2C%20so%20I%20was%20curious%20to%20see%20how%20this%20smaller%20brush%20fared.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20self-emptying%20base%20has%20three%20parts%20that%20assemble%20quickly%3A%20a%20main%20unit%20that%20plugs%20into%20a%20standard%20outlet%2C%20an%20ejectable%20dustbin%2C%20and%20a%20round%20mat%20that%20snaps%20onto%20the%20unit.%20The%20overall%20profile%20is%20fairly%20unobtrusive%2C%20but%20the%20dock%20needs%20to%20be%20placed%20against%20a%20wall%20with%20at%20least%201%20foot%20of%20clearance%20on%20either%20side%20and%202%20feet%20of%20clearance%20in%20front.%20I%20found%20such%20a%20place%20in%20the%20corner%20of%20my%20dining%20room.%20The%20base%20contains%20a%20HEPA%20filter%20to%20keep%20allergens%20locked%20in%20until%20the%20dustbin%20is%20ready%20to%20be%20emptied.%20Shark%20purports%20that%20the%20dustbin%20can%20hold%20up%20to%2060%20days%20of%20debris%2C%20but%20I've%20found%20that%20to%20be%20an%20exaggeration.%20I%20usually%20empty%20it%20every%20couple%20of%20weeks.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20robot%20has%20two%20attachments%3A%20a%20dry%20vacuum%20attachment%20and%20a%20mop%2Fvac%20combo%20attachment.%20Both%20slot%20into%20the%20back%20of%20the%20robot%20and%20click%20in%20easily.%20The%20dry%20vac%20attachment%20is%20ready%20to%20go%20as%20soon%20as%20it's%20installed%2C%20but%20the%20wet%20mop%2Fvac%20attachment%20requires%20a%20few%20extra%20steps%3A%20installing%20the%20mopping%20pad%20and%20filling%20the%20mopping%20reservoir.%20The%20side%20of%20the%20attachment%20has%20helpful%20fill%20lines%20that%20show%20you%20how%20much%20water%20and%20floor%20cleaner%20to%20add.%20The%20robot%20came%20with%20a%20small%20sampler%20bottle%20of%20Shark's%20own%20floor%20cleaner%2C%20but%20you%20can%20use%20only%20water%20or%20a%20floor%20cleaner%20of%20your%20choice.%20I've%20personally%20been%20using%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbi-auto-70244-20%26h%3D55fc9d140388e3053ce9cc7c244d1ca448f0fbc731511232523ee2292f4b1508%26postID%3D6655db8542ab0c2431cbc960%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Fhome%252Fshark-matrix-plus-2-in-1-robot-vacuum-mop-review%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.amazon.com%252FWindex-Multi-Surface-Disinfectant-Cleaner-Fluid-Ounce%252Fdp%252FB01GFLZ46W%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWindex%20all-purpose%20cleaner%3C%2Fa%3E%20since%20my%20sample%20bottle%20ran%20out.%20Importantly%2C%20the%20robot%20only%20self-empties%20into%20the%20base%20when%20the%20dry%20vacuum%20attachment%20is%20installed.%20If%20you're%20using%20the%20mop%2Fvac%20attachment%2C%20you'll%20have%20to%20empty%20the%20debris%20yourself%20when%20the%20robot%20is%20done%20cleaning.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225712%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22close%20up%20of%20the%20mopping%20attachment%20for%20the%20Shark%20Matrix%20robot%20vacuum%20showing%20fill%20lines%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F666329cdcc442a2f676f20f1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224284%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EYou%20can%20use%20water%20only%20or%20a%20combination%20of%20water%20and%20floor%20cleaner%20with%20the%20mopping%20attachment.%20There%20are%20fill%20lines%20on%20the%20front%20of%20the%20attachment%20for%20both.%3Cp%3ELauren%20Savoie%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20get%20the%20full%20functionality%20of%20the%20robot%20vacuum%2C%20you%20need%20to%20download%20the%20Shark%20app%20on%20your%20phone.%20I%20was%20surprised%20to%20see%20that%20hardly%20any%20instructions%20were%20included%20in%20the%20box%20with%20the%20robot.%20Instead%2C%20the%20setup%20is%20almost%20entirely%20directed%20through%20the%20app.%20It%20walks%20you%20through%20setting%20up%20the%20base%2C%20connecting%20the%20robot%20to%20the%20WiFi%2C%20and%20conducting%20the%20robot's%20first%20exploratory%20run%20of%20your%20house%20to%20create%20a%20custom%20map.%20I%20found%20some%20of%20these%20setup%20instructions%20lacking%20and%20had%20to%20do%20some%20Googling%20for%20more%20in-depth%20instructions%20(I%20could%20not%20figure%20out%20how%20to%20attach%20the%20docking%20mat%20to%20the%20base)%2C%20but%20aside%20from%20a%20few%20hiccups%2C%20the%20setup%20was%20pretty%20straightforward.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20exploratory%20run%2C%20the%20robot%20basically%20wanders%20around%20your%20home%2C%20taking%20stock%20of%20walls%2C%20furniture%2C%20and%20other%20obstacles.%20Shark%20is%20tight-lipped%20on%20the%20exact%20technology%20it%20uses%20for%20navigation%2C%20but%20based%20on%20its%20design%20and%20my%20experience%20with%20other%20robot%20vacuums%2C%20I%20would%20venture%20it%20uses%20a%20combination%20of%20ceiling%20mapping%20to%20get%20a%20basic%20layout%20of%20the%20room%20and%20laser%20light%20detection%20and%20ranging%20(lidar)%20for%20more%20detailed%20obstacle%20detection.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221178%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22screenshot%20of%20the%20shark%20matrix%20app%20showing%20the%20map%20it%20made%20of%20a%20home%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66632d151cd3b17790446d7c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22884%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20partial%20screenshot%20of%20the%20map%20my%20robot%20made%20of%20my%20home.%20Once%20the%20robot%20produced%20a%20rough%20schematic%2C%20I%20went%20into%20the%20app%20and%20labeled%20the%20rooms%2C%20set%20no-go%20zones%20(shown%20with%20an%20x%20pattern)%2C%20and%20denoted%20carpeted%20areas%20(shown%20with%20a%20dotted%20pattern).%3Cp%3ELauren%20Savoie%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20exploratory%20run%20took%20about%2045%20minutes%2C%20and%20when%20it%20was%20done%2C%20a%20comprehensive%20and%20accurate%20map%20of%20my%20home%20was%20uploaded%20to%20my%20Shark%20app.%20From%20there%2C%20I%20was%20instructed%20to%20delineate%20the%20borders%20between%20rooms%20and%20give%20them%20names.%20I%20was%20also%20asked%20to%20set%20any%20no-go%20zones%20(I%20opted%20to%20set%20these%20up%20around%20my%20cat's%20food%20bowls%20and%20areas%20where%20we%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20wires)%20and%20mark%20any%20carpeted%20areas%20so%20that%20the%20robot%20avoids%20them%20when%20mopping.%20In%20addition%20to%20on-demand%20cleaning%2C%20you%20can%20use%20the%20app%20to%20set%20a%20cleaning%20schedule%20that%20the%20robot%20will%20automatically%20follow.%20(I%20chose%20not%20to%20because%20I%20have%20a%20very%20sensitive%20cat%20who%20gets%20freaked%20out%20when%20the%20robot%20is%20cleaning.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EOur%20review%20of%20the%20Shark%20Matrix%20vacuum%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20used%20the%20Shark%20Matrix%20Plus%202-in-1%20Robot%20Vacuum%20as%20part%20of%20my%20cleaning%20routine%20for%20months%20now%2C%20and%20it%20truly%20does%20feel%20like%20having%20a%20little%20Rosie%20the%20Robot%20to%20clean%20alongside%20me.%20Since%20owning%20the%20Shark%20Matrix%2C%20I've%20only%20had%20to%20break%20out%20my%20stick%20vacuum%20a%20few%20times%2C%20and%20usually%20just%20for%20quick%20spills%2Fspot%20cleans%20that%20I%20know%20would%20take%20the%20robot%20longer%20to%20address.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Ease%20of%20use%5C%22%3EEase%20of%20use%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20all%20robot%20vacuums%2C%20the%20Shark%20requires%20you%20to%20prep%20your%20space%20a%20bit%20before%20vacuuming%20or%20mopping.%20For%20me%2C%20this%20means%20picking%20up%20rogue%20cat%20toys%2C%20moving%20smaller%20furniture%20like%20dining%20chairs%2C%20and%20ensuring%20any%20cords%20are%20tucked%20away.%20A%20few%20minutes%20of%20tidying%20up%20the%20space%20helps%20you%20get%20the%20most%20out%20of%20the%20robot's%20cleaning.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it's%20time%20to%20run%20the%20robot%2C%20I%20make%20sure%20I%20have%20the%20right%20attachment%20installed%20and%20use%20the%20app%20to%20decide%20which%20rooms%20I%20want%20to%20clean%20and%20how%20much%20suction%20power%20I%20want%20the%20robot%20to%20use.%20Generally%2C%20the%20more%20suction%20power%20and%20the%20more%20rooms%20you%20have%20it%20clean%2C%20the%20longer%20it%20will%20take.%20For%20me%2C%20a%20whole%20home%20clean%20takes%20about%2090%20minutes%2C%20whereas%20a%20single%20200-square-foot%20room%20clean%20can%20take%20as%20little%20as%2010.%20The%20robot%20automatically%20senses%20whether%20the%20dry%20vac%20or%20wet%20mop%2Fvac%20is%20attached%20and%20tailors%20its%20cleaning%20accordingly.%20For%20example%2C%20when%20the%20wet%20mop%2Fvac%20attachment%20is%20installed%2C%20the%20robot%20will%20skip%20all%20carpeted%20rooms%20and%20area%20rugs%2C%20as%20long%20as%20you%20have%20them%20marked%20on%20your%20map.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22two%20screenshots%20of%20the%20sharx%20matrix%20app%20showing%20the%20main%20cleaning%20screen%20and%20an%20option%20to%20schedule%20later%20cleans%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66632f04d0b8e1c832cd1b5b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETwo%20screenshots%20from%20the%20Shark%20app%3A%20on%20the%20left%20is%20the%20main%20cleaning%20screen%20where%20you%20can%20choose%20between%20cleaning%20the%20whole%20home%2C%20specific%20rooms%2C%20or%20just%20a%20spot%20clean%20of%20a%20specific%20area.%20On%20the%20right%20is%20the%20scheduling%20screen%20where%20you%20can%20set%20up%20routine%20cleaning%20times.%3Cp%3ELauren%20Savoie%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20choose%20a%20single-room%20clean%2C%20you%20can%20opt%20for%20a%20%26quot%3BMatrix%26quot%3B%20clean.%20This%20is%20an%20extra%20deep%20clean%20where%20the%20robot%20moves%20in%20a%20grid-like%20pattern%20and%20makes%20multiple%20passes%20to%20get%20as%20much%20debris%20as%20possible%20up.%20I've%20used%20the%20Matrix%20function%20most%20often%20in%20our%20carpeted%20rooms%20because%20I've%20found%20that%20regular%2C%20deep%20vacuuming%20really%20helps%20control%20my%20dust%20allergies.%20Matrix%20cleaning%20takes%20significantly%20longer%20(typically%20around%2045%20minutes%20for%20our%20bedroom)%2C%20but%20it%20is%20definitely%20the%20most%20thorough%20cleaning%20mode%20available%20on%20the%20Shark.%20I%20notice%20a%20significant%20difference%20in%20how%20the%20carpeting%20looks%20after%20a%2015-minute%20standard%20clean%20versus%20a%2045-minute%20Matrix%20clean.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20doing%20a%20Matrix%20clean%2C%20multi-room%20clean%2C%20or%20whole-home%20clean%2C%20the%20robot%20will%20return%20to%20the%20base%20every%2030%20minutes%20to%20empty%20itself%2C%20after%20which%20it'll%20resume%20cleaning%20where%20it%20left%20off.%20On%20the%20rare%20occasion%20I%20have%20it%20do%20a%20whole-home%20clean%2C%20the%20robot%20also%20usually%20needs%20to%20return%20to%20its%20base%20to%20recharge%20once%20before%20completing%20the%20clean.%20Once%20it%20does%2C%20it%20will%20again%20pick%20up%20where%20it%20left%20off.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Cleaning%20performance%5C%22%3ECleaning%20performance%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EI%20find%20myself%20using%20the%20wet%20mop%2Fvac%20attachment%20most%20often.%20This%20attachment%20allows%20the%20robot%20to%20vacuum%20and%20mop%20simultaneously%2C%20which%20I%20find%20most%20useful%20since%20most%20of%20our%20living%20areas%20have%20hard%20flooring.%20The%20technology%20isn't%20groundbreaking%20here%3A%20a%20water%20tank%20deposits%20a%20steady%20stream%20of%20water%20and%20floor%20cleaner%20onto%20a%20cloth%20cleaning%20rag%20that%20velcros%20onto%20the%20attachment.%20Since%20it%20sits%20behind%20the%20brush%20roll%2C%20the%20robot%20can%20vacuum%20first%20before%20the%20mopping%20pad%20follows%20behind%20to%20Swiffer%20the%20area.%20The%20robot%20wiggles%20side%20to%20side%20while%20mopping%20to%20loosen%20up%20any%20stuck-on%20debris%2C%20but%20you'll%20need%20to%20address%20really%20tough%20and%20sticky%20spills%20or%20stains%20by%20hand.%20Still%2C%20I%20find%20it%20does%20a%20really%20great%20job%20of%20handling%20everyday%20dirt%20and%20dust%20and%20making%20floors%20look%20fresh.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20my%20cat%20and%20I%20are%20prolific%20shedders%2C%20and%20the%20robot%20does%20a%20solid%20job%20of%20picking%20up%20all%20our%20hair.%20I've%20noticed%20that%20the%20cat%20hair%20can%20sometimes%20ball%20up%20and%20get%20stuck%20in%20the%20inflow%20port%20when%20using%20the%20wet%20mop%2Fvac%20attachment.%20Since%20this%20attachment%20needs%20to%20be%20manually%20emptied%2C%20I%20usually%20just%20pull%20the%20ball%20out%20when%20I'm%20doing%20that%20task.%20My%20own%20hair%20causes%20more%20issues%3A%20it%20tends%20to%20wrap%20around%20the%20brush%20roll%20and%20extracting%20it%20can%20be%20a%20bit%20of%20a%20chore%2C%20but%20more%20on%20that%20below.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225712%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22a%20close%20up%20of%20the%20mopping%20attachment%20of%20the%20shark%20matrix%20robot%20vac%2C%20showing%20hair%20stuck%20in%20the%20inflow%20port%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66632aa81cd3b17790446a91%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224284%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAs%20shown%20here%2C%20cat%20hair%20and%20dust%20tends%20to%20ball%20up%20and%20get%20stuck%20in%20the%20intake%20port%20when%20using%20the%20mopping%20attachment.%3Cp%3ELauren%20Savoie%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20most%20robot%20vacuums%2C%20the%20Shark%20Matrix%20functions%20best%20when%20used%20nearly%20every%20day%20rather%20than%20for%20periodic%20deep%20cleaning.%20While%20the%20vacuum%20does%20a%20stellar%20job%20with%20everyday%20dust%2C%20dirt%2C%20and%20flour%20spills%2C%20it%20struggles%20a%20bit%20more%20with%20larger%20pieces%20of%20debris.%20I%20occasionally%20find%20cat%20treats%2C%20pieces%20of%20plastic%20food%20wrappers%2C%20and%20popcorn%20kernels%20rattling%20around%20in%20the%20space%20between%20the%20brush%20roll%20and%20the%20intake%20port.%20It's%20also%20prone%20to%20leaving%20some%20debris%20behind%20and%20does%20a%20mediocre%20job%20with%20corners%2C%20but%20you'll%20notice%20these%20shortfalls%20less%20if%20you%20use%20it%20to%20%3Cem%3Emaintain%20%3C%2Fem%3Eclean%20floors%20rather%20than%20expecting%20it%20to%20completely%20transform%20long-neglected%20floors.%20That%20said%2C%20the%20beauty%20of%20a%20robot%20vacuum%20is%20that%20you%20%3Cem%3Ecan%3C%2Fem%3E%20vacuum%20or%20mop%20every%20day%20without%20hardly%20lifting%20a%20finger.%20Since%20introducing%20this%20robot%20vacuum%20into%20my%20life%2C%20my%20floors%20have%20never%20looked%20so%20consistently%20clean.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Noise%5C%22%3ENoise%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20robot's%20noise%20level%20depends%20a%20lot%20on%20what%20setting%20you're%20using.%20The%20higher%20the%20suction%20setting%2C%20the%20more%20noise%20it%20will%20make%2C%20but%20even%20at%20the%20highest%20levels%2C%20I%20don't%20find%20it%20obtrusive%20or%20obnoxious.%20It%20does%20sound%20like%20someone%20is%20vacuuming%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0I%20don't%20think%20there's%20any%20way%20around%20that%2C%20but%20I%20can%20still%20hold%20a%20conversation%20or%20take%20a%20work%20meeting%20when%20it's%20running.%20The%20loudest%20part%20of%20the%20cleaning%20is%20when%20the%20robot%20empties%20into%20the%20self-cleaning%20base.%20This%20sounds%20a%20bit%20like%20the%20ignition%20in%20a%20car%20revving%20up%20and%20was%20startling%20the%20first%20time%20I%20heard%20it.%20Now%20I'm%20used%20to%20it%2C%20and%20it's%20only%20about%205%20seconds%20of%20loud%20noise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Maintenance%5C%22%3EMaintenance%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20not%20much%20to%20do%20in%20terms%20of%20day-to-day%20maintenance%20and%20cleaning.%20After%20using%20the%20mop%20attachment%2C%20I%20remove%20the%20wet%20mopping%20pad%20from%20the%20robot%20and%20throw%20it%20in%20the%20wash%20(though%20I%20admit%20I've%20let%20it%20sit%20a%20few%20days%20before%20%E2%80%94%20it%20eventually%20dries%20on%20its%20own%20and%20doesn't%20leave%20a%20wet%20spot%20on%20the%20floor).%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225712%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22the%20shark%20matrix%20robot%20vacuum%20shown%20attached%20to%20its%20dock%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66632ff9cc442a2f676f27d9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224284%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20vacuum%20empties%20itself%20into%20a%20dustbin%20attached%20to%20the%20charging%20dock.%20The%20dustbin%20pops%20out%20with%20the%20press%20of%20a%20button%20(shown%20in%20the%20top%20right%20corner%20of%20the%20dock)%20and%20only%20needs%20to%20be%20emptied%20every%20couple%20weeks.%3Cp%3ELauren%20Savoie%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20couple%20of%20weeks%2C%20I%20empty%20the%20dustbin%20from%20the%20dock.%20This%20is%20far%20more%20frequently%20than%20the%20advertised%2060-day%20dustbin%20capacity%2C%20but%20I%20don't%20really%20mind%20doing%20it%20once%20a%20fortnight.%20The%20dustbin%20easily%20pops%20out%20from%20the%20base%2C%20a%20button%20releases%20its%20contents%20into%20the%20trash%2C%20and%20then%20it%20pops%20right%20back%20into%20the%20base%20again.%20Every%20month%20or%20so%2C%20I%20have%20to%20grab%20a%20pair%20of%20scissors%20and%20release%20the%20spool%20of%20hair%20that%20has%20wound%20its%20way%20around%20the%20brush%20roll.%20I%20wish%20it%20had%20a%20quick%20release%20for%20hair%20like%20some%20other%20brush%20rolls%20I've%20seen%20since%20I'm%20always%20paranoid%20that%20I'm%20going%20to%20knick%20the%20bristles%20with%20my%20scissors%2C%20but%20anyone%20who%20has%20a%20lot%20of%20hair%20knows%20that%20this%20chore%20is%20just%20a%20fact%20of%20life%20for%20any%20vacuum.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Cons%20to%20consider%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ECons%20to%20consider%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20hallmark%20of%20a%20good%20robot%20vacuum%20is%20that%20it's%20unobtrusive%3A%20you%20set%20it%20to%20run%2C%20and%20it%20does%20its%20job%20without%20bothering%20you%20or%20constantly%20asking%20for%20attention.%20On%20most%20fronts%2C%20the%20Shark%20does%20a%20great%20job%20in%20that%20department%20%E2%80%94%20it%20empties%20itself%2C%20recharges%20itself%20when%20needed%2C%20and%20operates%20fairly%20quietly.%20However%2C%20I'd%20say%20once%20every%20four%20or%20five%20cleans%2C%20it%20needs%20some%20sort%20of%20attention%20because%20its%20brush%20roll%20is%20tangled%2C%20it's%20run%20out%20of%20cleaning%20fluid%2C%20or%20there's%20something%20stuck%20in%20the%20intake.%20This%20is%20pretty%20typical%20for%20robot%20vacuums%2C%20but%20what%20I%20find%20frustrating%20about%20the%20Shark%20is%20that%20it'll%20verbally%20announce%20its%20issue%20once%20and%20then%20never%20again.%20If%20you%20miss%20the%20first%20announcement%2C%20you%20have%20to%20play%20a%20guessing%20game%20of%20what's%20wrong%20with%20the%20robot.%20Curiously%2C%20the%20app%20usually%20doesn't%20help%20here.%20I'd%20expect%20the%20app%20to%20tell%20you%20what's%20wrong%20and%20what%20you%20need%20to%20do%20to%20remedy%20it.%20It%20only%20does%20so%20about%20half%20of%20the%20time.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20found%20that%20the%20app%2C%20in%20general%2C%20can%20be%20buggy.%20It%20often%20inexplicably%20logs%20me%20out.%20The%20most%20current%20glitch%20I've%20been%20experiencing%20(and%20it's%20been%20going%20on%20for%20several%20weeks)%20is%20that%20I%20often%20have%20trouble%20selecting%20multiple%20rooms%20to%20clean%20on%20my%20map.%20I%20have%20to%20close%20and%20reopen%20the%20app%20for%20full%20map%20functionality.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20good%20news%20is%20that%20apps%20are%20constantly%20being%20updated%2C%20so%20I%20expect%20these%20bugs%20to%20be%20addressed%20in%20time.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20other%20quibbles%20are%20that%20the%20robot%20does%20not%20self-empty%20when%20the%20wet%20mop%2Fvac%20attachment%20is%20installed%2C%20and%20the%20process%20of%20changing%20attachments%20based%20on%20whether%20you%20want%20to%20mop%20or%20not%20sometimes%20feels%20tedious.%20I'm%20sure%20there%20is%20a%20smart%20way%20to%20take%20a%20page%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fbest-wet-dry-vacuums%5C%22%3Ebest%20wet-dry%20vacuums%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20comb