0Costco's%20bosses%2C%20and%20Bernard%20Arnault.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EStarbucks%20legend%20Howard%20Schultz%20spilled%20the%20beans%20on%20the%20company's%20early%20days%2C%20shared%20some%20of%20his%20biggest%20regrets%2C%20and%20warned%20the%20coffee%20chain%20is%20on%20the%20wrong%20track%20in%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.acquired.fm%2Fepisodes%2Fstarbucks-with-howard-schultz%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eepic%20three-hour%20interview%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20Acquired%20podcast%2C%20released%20this%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchultz%20helped%20pioneer%20the%20coffeehouse%20concept%20in%20the%20US.%20He%20served%20as%20Starbucks'%20chairman%20and%20CEO%20from%201986%20to%202000%20and%20from%202008%20to%202017%2C%20and%20as%20interim%20CEO%20between%202022%20and%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20business%20guru%20also%20told%20the%20stories%20of%20how%20he%20crossed%20paths%20with%20Bill%20Gates%20Sr.%2C%20Steve%20Jobs%2C%20Costco's%20cofounders%2C%20Coke%20and%20Pepsi%2C%20and%20luxury%20tycoon%20Bernard%20Arnault.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20the%2012%20best%20nuggets%20from%20the%20episode%2C%20lightly%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%20Starbucks%20declined%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2202da1e59-38d2-44ed-99a5-90fffc214cc3%5C%22%3E1.%20Starbucks%20didn't%20sell%20its%20own%20coffee%20early%20on%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20Starbucks%20opened%20in%20Pike%20Place%20Market%20in%201971%2C%20they%20were%20using%20Peet's%20Coffee.%20No%20one%20knows%20that%2C%20that's%20new.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchultz%20said%20that%20before%20it%20began%20roasting%20its%20own%20coffee%2C%20the%20company%20brought%20Peet's%20Coffee%20from%20San%20Francisco%20to%20Seattle%2C%20repackaged%20it%2C%20and%20sold%20it%20under%20the%20Starbucks%20brand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220f9b2269-d203-4f6e-a1e2-f7da1f5100f6%5C%22%3E2.%20Italian%20coffee%20giant%20Lavazza%20turned%20down%20the%20chance%20to%20invest%20early%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Schultz%20was%20launching%20his%20Il%20Giornale%20coffee%20bar%20concept%2C%20he%20approached%20two%20Italian%20companies%20for%20financial%20backing%20but%20they%20turned%20him%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20never%20told%20this.%20One%20is%20the%20espresso%20company%20Faema%2C%20and%20one%20is%20the%20large%20Italian%20coffee%20company%20Lavazza%2C%20and%20I%20asked%20them%20both%20to%20invest%20in%20my%20idea%20and%20both%20of%20them%20turned%20me%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLavazza%20and%20Faema%2C%20just%20get%20that%20on%20the%20record%2C%20turned%20me%20down.%20They'll%20deny%20it.%20That's%20a%20fact.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223aee87c7-1274-463c-9f24-1b487a328693%5C%22%3E3.%20Bill%20Gates'%20dad%20helped%20Schultz%20buy%20Starbucks%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Schultz%20was%20raising%20money%20to%20buy%20Starbucks%20from%20its%20founders%20in%20the%20late%201980s%2C%20one%20of%20his%20investors%20made%20a%20cash%20offer%20for%20the%20company%20in%20a%20bid%20to%20cut%20him%20out%20of%20the%20deal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchultz%20secured%20a%20meeting%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbill-gates-sr-father-microsoft-cofounder-bill-gates-dies-2020-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBill%20Gates%20Sr.%3C%2Fa%3E%20through%20a%20friend.%20After%20the%20top%20lawyer%20and%20father%20of%20the%20Microsoft%20cofounder%20heard%20his%20story%2C%20he%20walked%20him%20over%20to%20the%20offices%20of%20the%20investor%20in%20question%2C%20Samuel%20Stroum%2C%20and%20in%20Schultz's%20telling%2C%20said%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20know%20what%20you%20are%20planning%2C%20but%20whatever%20it%20is%2C%20it's%20not%20going%20to%20happen.%20Howard%20Shultz%20is%20going%20to%20acquire%20Starbucks%20Coffee%20Company%2C%20and%20he's%20never%20going%20to%20hear%20from%20you%20again.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20only%20did%20Gates%20see%20off%20that%20threat%2C%20he%20also%20helped%20finance%20Schultz's%20takeover%20of%20Starbucks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Bill%20Gates%2C%20father%2C%20Bill%20Gates%20Sr.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F666303591cd3b17790444865%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBill%20Gates%20Sr.%20and%20Bill%20Gates.%3Cp%3EBrian%20Ach%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c4210ba1-25d1-4e57-be8e-57dbffcd32fe%5C%22%3E4.%20Schultz%20regrets%20not%20snagging%20the%20rights%20to%20two%20innovations%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Schultz%20was%20sourcing%20a%20better%20coffee%20cup%20and%20lid%20for%20Starbucks%20than%20the%20traditional%20Styrofoam%2C%20the%20Chicago%20paper%20company%20he%20enlisted%20struck%20gold.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20found%20a%20lid%2C%20that%20beautiful%20sip%20lid%2C%20which%20is%20now%20ubiquitous%20in%20the%20world.%20Howard%20Schultz%20should%20have%20said%20to%20them%2C%20'I%20want%20an%20exclusive%20on%20that%20lid%2C'%20because%20that%20lid%20became%20the%20standard%20for%20the%20world.%20If%20I%20would%20have%20just%20understood%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20other%20thing%20I%20didn't%20do%20is%20we%20introduced%20caff%C3%A8%20latte%20to%20America%20but%20we%20didn't%20trademark%20it.%20We%20trademarked%20Frappuccino%20later%20on%2C%20but%20we%20didn't%20trademark%20cafe%20latte.%20I%20wasn't%20thinking%3B%20I%20missed%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b53dc973-3074-4fee-9a8e-58483099df64%5C%22%3E5.%20Partnering%20with%20Costco%20and%20United%20Airlines%20ruffled%20some%20feathers%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECostco%20cofounder%20Jeff%20Brotman%20helped%20finance%20Schultz's%20takeover%20of%20Starbucks%20in%201987%20and%20was%20an%20early%20board%20member%2C%20and%20Brotman%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fcostco-hot-dog-c