of%20the%20electric%20car%20maker%20will%20decide%20on%20Mr%20Musk's%20compensation%20package%20on%20June%2013.%20This%20will%20be%20the%20second%20time%20that%20shareholders%20will%20vote%20on%20the%20CEO's%20compensation%20which%20was%20first%20ruled%20invalid%20earlier%20this%20year%20by%20a%20Delaware%20court%20who%20claimed%20that%20the%20approval%20process%20was%20%26quot%3Bdeeply%20flawed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMs%20Denholm%20wrote%20in%20the%20letter%20to%20shareholders%2C%20filed%20with%20the%20Securities%20and%20Exchange%20Commission%2C%20%26quot%3BElon%20is%20not%20a%20typical%20executive%2C%20and%20Tesla%20is%20not%20a%20typical%20company.%20So%2C%20the%20typical%20way%20in%20which%20companies%20compensate%20key%20executives%20is%20not%20going%20to%20drive%20results%20for%20Tesla.%20Motivating%20someone%20like%20Elon%20requires%20something%20different.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20we%20recognized%20in%202018%20and%20continue%20to%20recognize%20today%20is%20that%20one%20thing%20Elon%20most%20certainly%20does%20not%20have%20is%20unlimited%20time.%20Nor%20does%20he%20face%20any%20shortage%20of%20ideas%20and%20other%20places%20he%20can%20make%20an%20incredible%20difference%20in%20the%20world.%20We%20want%20those%20ideas%2C%20that%20energy%20and%20that%20time%20to%20be%20at%20Tesla%2C%20for%20the%20benefit%20of%20you%2C%20our%20owners.%20But%20that%20requires%20reciprocal%20respect%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20continued.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20billionaire's%20other%20ventures%20including%20SpaceX%2C%20X%20and%20xAI%2C%20have%20concerned%20investors%20about%20his%20ability%20to%20focus%20on%20Tesla.%20Ms%20Denholm%20insisted%20that%20the%20vote%20to%20accept%20the%20%2456%20billion%20compensation%20plan%20is%20%26quot%3Bnot%20about%20the%20money%2C%26quot%3B%20even%20if%20it%20would%20make%20Mr%20Musk%20the%20highest-paid%20CEO%20in%20modern%20history.%20%26quot%3BWe%20all%20know%20Elon%20is%20one%20of%20the%20wealthiest%20people%20on%20the%20planet%2C%20and%20he%20would%20remain%20so%20even%20if%20Tesla%20were%20to%20renege%20on%20the%20commitment%20we%20made%20in%202018%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%202018%20deal%20was%20made%20in%20order%20to%20%26quot%3Bkeep%20Elon%20focused%20on%20Tesla%20and%20motivated%20to%20achieve%20the%20company's%20incomparable%20ambitions%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20Ms%20Denholm's%20letter.%20%26quot%3BUpholding%20our%20end%20of%20the%20bargain%2C%20then%2C%20by%20ratifying%20the%20decision%20we%20all%20made%20in%202018%2C%20is%20more%20important%20than%20ever.%20If%20Tesla%20is%20to%20retain%20Elon's%20attention%20and%20motivate%20him%20to%20continue%20to%20devote%20his%20time%2C%20energy%2C%20ambition%20and%20vision%20to%20deliver%20comparable%20results%20in%20the%20future%2C%20we%20must%20stand%20by%20our%20deal%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20Mr%20Musk%20is%20looking%20to%20acquire%20a%2025%20per%20cent%20interest%20in%20Tesla%2C%20which%20would%20give%20him%20more%20influence%20over%20the%20company%20to%20accomplish%20his%20objectives%20of%20creating%20artificial%20intelligence%20and%20self-driving%20vehicles.%20He%20has%20also%20threatened%20to%20split%20off%20Tesla's%20AI%20research%20into%20a%20different%20company%20if%20his%20demands%20are%20not%20satisfied.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%2C%20the%20board%20chair%20also%20urged%20shareholders%20to%20approve%20moving%20the%20company's%20base%20to%20Texas.%20Tesla%20was%20incorporated%20in%20the%20US%20state%20of%20Delaware%2C%20but%20Mr%20Musk%20moved%20to%20change%20its%20registration%20to%20Texas%2C%20where%20the%20company%20headquarters%20are%20located%2C%20as%20per%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Ftechnology%2Farticle%2F2024%2Fjun%2F07%2Felon-musk-may-step-back-if-shareholders-reject-56bn-pay-package-tesla-chair-warns%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ethe%20Guardian%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1717923480000%2C%22visual%22%3A